gomodel:SYNGO_792  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper charactrerizes EAAT4 as a L-glutamate and L-aspartate transporter that shuttles these across membranes in a sodium-dependent manner.\n\nTable 1 summarized the results of an 3H-L-glutamate and 3H-L-aspartate uptake assays in Xenopus oocytes expressing the transporter. Injected oocytes had a 30-fold higher uptake of the compounds than uninjected controls.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has \"glutamate transmembrane transporter activity\" and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'neurotransmitter uptake (GO:0001504)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[O35921] SynGO ID 771 (PMID:9570792, EM). Experimental description: '... were used to amplify complementary DNAs from human cerebellar messenger RNA.'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2018-07-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_792" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

